  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adults patients of ASA physical status I and II, aged 20-70 year who will be scaduled
             for Maxillo - facial cancer surgeries

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with disfigurement and disturbed anatomy that will not allow easy access to
             the sphenopalatine ganglion, bleeding disorders, history of hepatic, renal or
             cardiopulmonary dysfunction, patients receiving drugs affecting coagulation or
             cardiovascular active medication are excluded also patients having infection or
             allergies to local anesthetics
      </textblock>
